        <num>CC 492</num>
        <heading>492.  Separate ownership of part of a building</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 492.  Separate ownership of part of a building.
Separate ownership of a part of a building, such as a floor, an apartment, or a room, may be established only by a juridical act of the owner of the entire building when and in the manner expressly authorized by law.</p>
        </content>
